definitions.definition: To move with a sharp turn or reversal.
The unit of currency of Zaire.
A form of seated meditation in Zen Buddhism.
The fervour or tireless devotion for a person, cause, or ideal and determination in its furtherance; diligent enthusiasm; powerful interest.
definitions.example: She extols the virtues of veganism with missionary zeal.

definitions.definition: A person who exhibits such fervour or tireless devotion.
The collective noun for a group of zebras.
One who is zealous, one who is full of zeal for his own specific beliefs or objectives, usually in the negative sense of being too passionate; a fanatic

A member of a radical, warlike, ardently patriotic group of Jews in Judea, particularly prominent in the first century, who advocated the violent overthrow of Roman rule and vigorously resisted the efforts of the Romans and their supporters to convert the Jews.
A member of an anti-aristocratic political group in Thessalonica from 1342 until 1350.
Full of zeal; ardent, fervent; exhibiting enthusiasm or strong passion.
Any of three species of genus Equus: E. grevyi, E. quagga, or E. zebra, all with black and white stripes and native to Africa.
A referee.
An unlikely diagnosis, especially for symptoms probably caused by a common ailment. (Originates in the advice often given to medical students: "when you hear hoofbeats, think of horses, not zebras".)
A biracial person, specifically one born to a member of the Sub-Saharan African race and a Caucasian.
A fish, the zebra cichlid.
Any of various papilionid butterflies of the subgenus Paranticopsis of the genus Graphium, having black and white markings.
The point in the sky vertically above a given position or observer; the point in the celestial sphere opposite the nadir.
The highest point in the sky reached by a celestial body.
(by extension) Highest point or state; peak.
definitions.example: Winning the continental championship was the zenith of my career.

definitions.definition: The numeric symbol that represents the cardinal number zero.
definitions.example: In unary and k-adic notation in general, zero is the empty string.

definitions.definition: The digit 0 in the decimal, binary, and all other base numbering systems.
definitions.example: One million has six zeroes.

definitions.definition: Nothing, or none.
definitions.example: He knows zero about humour.

definitions.definition: The value of a magnitude corresponding to the cardinal number zero.
definitions.example: The electromagnetic field does not drop all of the way to zero before a reversal.

definitions.definition: The point on a scale at which numbering or measurement originates.
definitions.example: The temperature outside is ten degrees below zero.

definitions.definition: A value of the independent variables of a function, for which the function is equal to zero.
definitions.example: The derivative of a continuous, differentiable function that twice crosses the axis must have a zero.

definitions.definition: The additive identity element of a monoid or greater algebraic structure, particularly a group or ring.
definitions.example: Since a commutative zero is the inverse of any additive identity, it must be unique when it exists.

definitions.definition: A person of little or no importance.
definitions.example: They rudely treated him like a zero.

definitions.definition: A Mitsubishi A6M Zero, a long range fighter aircraft operated by the Japanese Navy Air Service from 1940 to 1945.
A setting of calibrated instruments such as a firearm.
A security which has a zero coupon (paying no periodic interest).
definitions.example: The takeovers were financed by issuing zeroes.

definitions.definition: To set a measuring instrument to zero; to calibrate instrument scale to valid zero.
definitions.example: Zero the fluorometer with the same solvent used in extraction.

definitions.definition: To change a memory location or range to values of zero; to set a variable in a computer program to zero.
definitions.example: Results were inconsistent because an array wasn’t zeroed during initialization.

definitions.definition: To cause or set some value or amount to be zero.
definitions.example: They tried to zero the budget by the end of the quarter.

definitions.definition: To eliminate; to delete; to overwrite with zeros.
To disappear
